genresAdvancedInfo.name: chinese experimental
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Chinese experimental music is a genre that pushes the boundaries of traditional music by incorporating unconventional sounds, techniques, and instruments. It often features avant-garde compositions, improvisation, and soundscapes that challenge listeners' expectations and perceptions of what music can be. Chinese experimental music draws on a wide range of influences, including traditional Chinese music, Western classical music, and contemporary electronic and experimental music. It is a genre that is constantly evolving and pushing the limits of what is possible in music.
